  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "Removing a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list can be done in a few steps. Here's how you can do it:\n\n### On Mobile App:\n1. **Open Facebook Messenger:** Launch the Messenger app on your mobile device.\n2. **Find the Contact:** Scroll through your contact list or use the search function to locate the non-friend you want to remove.\n3. **Tap on the Contact:** Open the conversation with the contact.\n4. **Tap on Contact's Name:** At the top of the chat screen, tap on the contact\u2019s name to open their profile.\n5. **Manage:** Look for an option like \"Manage\" or \"More\" (the wording may vary slightly depending on updates to the app).\n6. **Block or Remove:** Select \"Block\" or \"Remove Contact.\" Blocking will prevent them from contacting you and remove them from your contact list.\n\n### On Desktop:\n1. **Open Facebook Messenger:** Go to the Facebook website and click on the Messenger icon, or go directly to messenger.com.\n2. **Find the Contact:** Use the search bar to find the non-friend contact.\n3. **Open Chat:** Click on the conversation with the contact.\n4. **Click on the Contact\u2019s Name:** At the top of the chat window, click on the contact\u2019s name to open their profile or settings.\n5. **Block or Remove:** Look for options such as \"Block\" or \"Remove Contact.\" Blocking will remove them from your contact list and prevent future interactions.\n\n### Additional Steps if Needed:\n- **Remove Synced Contacts:** If the contact was synced from your phone contacts, you might need to disable contact syncing in Messenger settings.\n  1. **Open Messenger Settings:** Go to your profile icon or settings in Messenger.\n  2. **People:** Find and select the \"People\" option.\n  3. **Upload Contacts:** Turn off the \"Upload Contacts\" option and delete synced contacts if necessary.\n\nRemember, blocking someone will not notify them that they have been blocked, but they will no longer be able to send you messages or see your profile on Messenger.",
